<L>__{interior prison morning}
<A>__{max's cell door opens. he walks, happy and confident this morning.}
<C>__{inmate}
<P>__{(calling out)}
<D>__{hey barber, tomorrow lunch, right?}
<C>__{max}
<D>__{right.}
<C>__{another convict}
<D>__{give `em hell!}
<C>__{max}
<D>__{i always do, felipe!}
<A>__{as max reaches the end of the walkway, an old guard opens the next steel door for him.}
<C>__{guard}
<D>__{morning, max. here we are again.}
<C>__{max}
<D>__{how's your grandson?}
<C>__{guard}
<D>__{just started first grade.}
<C>__{max}
<D>__{that's great. the socialization begins!}
<A>__{the guard smiles as he leads him toward the parole board room at the end of another long corridor. they stop at the door.}
<C>__{guard}
<D>__{how many more of these you think you got in you, max?}
<A>__{pause.}
<C>__{max}
<D>__{as many as it takes.}
<A>__{the guard shakes his head, opens the door for him.}
